Moreover, there is a rising demand for non-invasive diagnostic techniques that offer accurate and reliable results while minimizing patient discomfort and risks. Liquid biopsy-based tests, imaging techniques like MRI and PET scans, and molecular diagnostic assays are gaining traction in the market due to their ability to provide valuable information about the presence, progression, and prognosis of prostate cancer.

