Furthermore, regulatory initiatives and guidelines aimed at improving the quality of prostate cancer diagnostics are shaping the market landscape. Stringent regulations related to the approval and commercialization of diagnostic tests are driving companies to invest in robust clinical validation studies and adhere to strict quality control measures to ensure the reliability and accuracy of their products.

